  "market_context": "Intraday session after London manipulation, price swept a prior low on the hourly chart, then executed an aggressive upward displacement. Analyst waited for RTH open (~09:30 EST) before dropping to 5-minute for entry.",
  "key_observation": "After sweeping a low, price showed aggressive return up; the analyst identified the 0.62 Fibonacci retracement (3844.00) as the OTE zone on the 5-minute chart, with stop below the swept low and target at the internal high (3857.0).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst observed the hourly chart showing a green candle closing at 3845, establishing bullish bias after a low sweep and aggressive recovery.",
    "Step 2: Identified the prior low (around 3825.75–3829.00) as the liquidity sweep point and the internal high (3857.0) as the target zone.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the 5-minute chart post-09:30 RTH open and marked the OTE zone using Fibonacci levels: 0.79 at 3827.5, 0.62 at 3844.0, and 0.5 at 3857.0.",
    "Step 4: Defined entry at 0.62 (3844.0), stop just below the swept low (~3829.0), and target at the internal high (3857.0), aligning with the hourly bias."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit the internal high target (3857.0) on the 5-minute chart, confirming the setup worked as intended.",
  "lessons": "Using higher-time-frame bias (hourly) to guide lower-time-frame entries (5-min) increases probability; OTE at 0.62 after a low sweep with aggressive return offers tight risk and clear internal target.",
